  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal constitutes development under the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and the local planning authority is not satisfied that, based on the drawings submitted as part of the application, this proposal falls within any class of 'permitted development' specified within Schedule 2 to the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n\r\nINFORMATIVE: The proposed development fails to comply with condition A.1 (f), (h), (i), (ja) and A.3 (c) of Class A and condition B.2 b)(bb)ii) of Class B of Part 1, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) as, the proposed extension would exceed 3m depth, 4m in height and would be within 7m of a rear boundary; would be located within 2m of a boundary with eaves exceeding 3m height; would not contain the same roof pitch as the original dwelling; and being located above the existing two-storey addition would adjoin an extension and not the original dwelling house whilst also extending beyond an outside face of an external wall of the original dwelling house. "
